what is shebang
echo $name will print the value of the variable 'name' in the terminal.
$ is a special character used in shell scripting to denote a variable.
 When you use $name, it retrieves the value stored in the variable 'name' and displays it in the terminal.
what are exit codes
echo $? will print the exit code of the last executed command. Exit codes are numerical values returned by commands to indicate their success or failure.
 A value of 0 typically indicates success,
 while any non-zero value indicates an error or failure.

